![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1624477734220-CYCJR9QQSCGXSR2RN0EZ/Burning183.jpg)

When people think of their favorite cinematic versions of Superman they tend to be split. Traditionalists will point to Christopher Reeve, and his series of films that made us "Believe A Man Could Fly". Others call the Reeve version "outdated", celebrating and favoring Henry Cavill's Man of Steel above all others. Right in the middle, sits Brandon Routh and his portrayal of the Big Blue Boyscout in Superman Returns. Join us as we look back 15 years at the film that was set to take Superman to new heights before the DCEU even existed!

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](../episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
